</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="5CF6589A920EFFC9FF08F8C1ED7EF845" pageId="9" pageNumber="522" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="14530B11920EFFC9FF08F8C1ECA8F8C5" blockId="9.[132,775,1874,2028]" box="[132,232,1874,1900]" pageId="9" pageNumber="522">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B11920EFFC9FF08F8E2ED7EF845" blockId="9.[132,775,1874,2028]" pageId="9" pageNumber="522">
The presence of mandibulate polymorphs and the dummy shaped orifices serve to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920EFFC9FD9CF801EE2FF802" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[528,623,1938,1963]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="9" pageNumber="522" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="voigti">
<emphasis id="2698D703920EFFC9FD9CF801EE2FF802" box="[528,623,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="522">D. voigti</emphasis>
